Part 3 – Enhancing Functionality and SEO
Overview

Part 3 focuses on improving the website’s usability, interactivity, search engine visibility, and form functionality. This includes the addition of JavaScript-based interactive components, AJAX form handling, SEO enhancements, accessibility improvements, and required documentation. All updates below have been implemented and tested.

1. JavaScript Enhancements
Interactive Elements

Accordion Functionality:
Implemented expandable/collapsible accordion sections to organize content and improve readability.

Lightbox Gallery:
Added a JavaScript lightbox that displays images in a modal when clicked, enhancing the user’s viewing experience.

Search Filter System:
A dynamic search field filters items in real time using data attributes (data-title) on product or content cards.

Leaflet Interactive Map:
Created a new page (locations.html) featuring a Leaflet.js interactive map with markers and popups for location display.

Advanced DOM Manipulation:
Used JS to dynamically toggle elements, handle modals, validate forms, and update page content based on user actions.

2. Dynamic Content Loading

Added JavaScript-driven content filtering for product/service listings.

Integrated AJAX form handling to send data to a local API endpoint without reloading the page.

Implemented fallback behavior using mailto: or client-side estimates when the server is unavailable.

3. Search Engine Optimization (SEO)
Keyword Research

Researched and incorporated keywords such as:

rocket resellers, affordable devices, refurbished tech, electronic repairs.

On-Page SEO Improvements

Meta Titles & Descriptions:
Added and updated meta tags for every page to ensure clarity and keyword alignment.

Header Structure (H1–H3):
Ensured proper heading hierarchy through all pages.

Image Optimization:
Added meaningful alt text and improved image naming conventions.

Internal Linking:
Cross-linked relevant pages to improve crawlability.

Clean URL Structure:
Ensured filenames and paths remain descriptive and SEO-friendly.

Mobile Responsiveness:
Verified layout functionality on small, medium, and large devices.

Technical SEO

sitemap.xml created and updated automatically with all site pages.

robots.txt added to guide search engine crawlers.

Page Speed Optimisation:
Compressing images, deferring scripts, and reducing unused CSS.

Structured Data (JSON-LD):
Added “WebPage” schema to each page for improved search visibility.

Off-Page SEO Strategies (Documented)

Suggested backlink sources (blogs, local listings, partnerships).

Recommended social media content strategy.

Added location-based data for future local SEO integration.

4. Form Functionality and Validation
Enquiry Form (enquiry.html)

Purpose: Allows users to enquire about products, services, volunteering, or sponsorship.
Features:

HTML5 + JavaScript validation

Checks phone number format, required fields, and length

AJAX submission to /api/enquiry with fallback client-side processing

Displays cost/availability response dynamically

Contact Form (contact.html)

Purpose: Allows users to send general messages to the organisation.
Features:

Fields for name, email, phone, subject type, and full message

JS validation for email/phone formats

AJAX submission to /api/contact

Fallback mailto: link if API is unavailable

